I&rsquo;ve been seeing a lot of .URL will be deprecated... warnings in my Hugo compilations lately, and just now figured out a slick replacement for it: canonifyURLs = true. The documentation for this parameter says&hellip;
By default, all relative URLs encountered in the input are left unmodified, e.g. /css/foo.css would stay as /css/foo.css. The canonifyURLs field in your site config has a default value of false.
By setting canonifyURLs to true, all relative URLs would instead be canonicalized using baseURL. For example, assuming you have baseURL = https://example.
